Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[ed]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1044 \N"The Deadly Pork Soup Signal"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[op]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.64,0:00:03.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.51,0:00:07.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure always says some \Nkind of incident often happens
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.01,0:00:09.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,when we're hanging out together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.61,0:00:11.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.51,0:00:13.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's what you call a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.89,0:00:15.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.44,0:00:17.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So, is that a coincidence, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.16,0:00:23.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, what a coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.77,0:00:28.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It comes to visit after falling asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.39,0:00:30.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Fall in love with logical deduction \Nand the pleasure of solving mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.51,0:00:32.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Put your life on the line as \Nyou put the pot over the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.10,0:00:33.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a message hidden in the vegetables!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.57,0:00:35.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.19,0:00:36.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.97,0:00:39.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.99,0:02:28.00,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(402,1)}The Deadly Pork Soup Signal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.67,0:02:25.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Deadly Pork Soup Signal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.26,0:02:38.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim is Lisa \NHewitson-san, 25 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.98,0:02:41.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The cause of death is \Nshock due to blood loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:42.85,Lisa,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Lisa Hewitson (25) \NFloor Staff
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.32,0:02:45.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The estimated time of death \Nis between 1:00AM and 1:30AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.80,0:02:52.15,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by how much blood she lost, the \Nculprit probably got her blood on themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.30,0:02:53.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.64,0:02:55.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:57.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mori-san? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.42,0:02:59.15,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan-kun, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:03.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't found a weapon yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.24,0:03:04.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What about fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.38,0:03:09.29,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We found three sets of fingerprints \Nother than the victim's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.57,0:03:11.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.03,0:03:12.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.24,0:03:16.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What was inside that pouch?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:19.01,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,They're on that table over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.33,0:03:22.35,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Her ID, wallet, and various cosmetics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:25.14,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,There was a ball-point pen and notepad, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.67,0:03:29.52,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,There were no signs the front door \Nor windows were forced open, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.52,0:03:32.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This may have been the \Nwork of an acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.46,0:03:37.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then we should talk to the boyfriend first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.45,0:03:43.66,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Hara Takashi-san, 23 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.11,0:03:48.56,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to confirm with their \Nacquaintances that he was dating the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.06,0:03:52.97,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, the fingerprints collected \Nwhen he committed a traffic violation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.97,0:03:55.92,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,matched the fingerprints \Nfound at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.09,0:03:59.67,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wh-What?! I can't believe Lisa was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.29,0:03:59.46,Hara,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(363,305)}Hara Takashi (23) \NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.41,0:04:04.18,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,But she was so full of life yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.86,0:04:07.68,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you met \Nwith Lisa-san yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:13.19,Nameplate,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Hara
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.13,0:04:09.90,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:13.19,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday evening we spoke on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:18.69,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you last night \Nbetween 1:00AM and 1:30AM?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.10,0:04:24.57,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,Last night I was drinking \Nwith my coworkers until 3AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.05,0:04:29.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, did you notice anything \Nunusual about her recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.09,0:04:31.41,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,Anything unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.72,0:04:34.14,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Like suspicious persons hanging around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.14,0:04:35.29,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,It was him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:38.37,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,Komaki, the owner of the \Nstore Lisa worked at.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:41.34,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,She always complained \Nabout him hitting on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.73,0:04:44.74,DCMain,HARA,0000,0000,0000,,He must've done it. You have to arrest him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.95,0:04:48.41,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Komaki Satoshi-san, 47 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.41,0:04:50.85,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Previous offenses include tax \Nevasion and attempted extortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:54.60,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,According to rumors, he has connections \Nto some rather rough individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.16,0:04:59.00,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, his fingerprints were \Nalso found at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.86,0:05:01.36,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.11,0:05:05.90,Komaki,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(317, 304)}Komaki Satoshi (47) \NBar Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.28,0:05:06.61,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Officer, you don't think I did it, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.93,0:05:08.77,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.77,0:05:12.12,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that one of your employees is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.53,0:05:14.40,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We need to speak with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.02,0:05:16.46,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.79,0:05:21.41,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I promise \Nmy complete cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.44,0:05:27.13,DCMain,TAKASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell us about your \Nrelationship with Hewitson-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:31.39,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Officially, we had an \Nemployment relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.89,0:05:35.06,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, we were an \Nemployer and his employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.24,0:05:37.44,DCMain,TAKASHI,0000,0000,0000,,And privately?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.10,0:05:44.32,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange for a little pocket money, \Nwe played Old Maid together late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.56,0:05:45.14,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.14,0:05:49.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you've been \Ninside Hewitson-san's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.19,0:05:52.28,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:55.33,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Old Maid is a game you play at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.18,0:06:02.25,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell us your alibi \Nfor between 1:00AM and 1:30AM?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.50,0:06:07.63,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, now. Aren't there more important \Nthings you should be investigating?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.04,0:06:12.55,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about the conclusive \Nevidence left inside her home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:14.18,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you found something, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:17.53,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Like a bloody weapon, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.53,0:06:20.72,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Or a wine bottle with fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:23.90,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Or the jacket the culprit was wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.06,0:06:27.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.35,0:06:28.04,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.84,0:06:33.50,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know something about the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.50,0:06:36.54,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. I was just, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.54,0:06:39.66,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I know. It's because he did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.66,0:06:41.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He who?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.42,0:06:43.92,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about that brat Hara.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.32,0:06:48.09,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,He was always making eyes at my employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.42,0:06:51.22,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,So he must've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.60,0:06:54.39,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think that's too \Nmuch of a logical leap?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.78,0:06:56.42,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.42,0:06:58.14,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's definitely the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.51,0:07:01.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you're not the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.83,0:07:03.40,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:09.52,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You still haven't told us your alibi \Nfor between 1:00AM and 1:30AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.52,0:07:10.65,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,My alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:14.64,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,My alibi, huh? I've got that covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.29,0:07:18.66,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I've got an ironclad alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.94,0:07:21.17,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I was at home during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.17,0:07:25.17,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I'm lying, ask my wife Mihoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.60,0:07:29.92,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Komaki Mihoko-san, 28 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.19,0:07:31.60,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,No previous offenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:36.01,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Since they married two years \Nago, she's been his housewife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.28,0:07:41.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But can we really trust that \Nman's wife's testimony?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.34,0:07:47.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The credibility of her testimony \Nprobably comes with a question mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.04,0:07:52.03,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Before they married, when she worked \NKomaki's bar like the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:54.90,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,he pressured her into marrying him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.48,0:07:59.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If he's having his wife provide \Nfalse testimony, that works for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.34,0:08:04.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I, the great detective Mori Kogoro,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.48,0:08:09.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,will identify any contradictions in \Nher testimony and solve the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.54,0:08:18.77,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.77,0:08:20.08,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.21,0:08:26.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're definitely Komaki Mihoko-san, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.65,0:08:30.48,Mihoko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Komaki Mihoko (28) \NKomaki Satoshi's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.76,0:08:28.93,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes. Ask me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.48,0:08:34.91,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,My husband insisted I answer \Nall your questions truthfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.13,0:08:40.16,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Then what time did Komaki-san \Ncome home last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.19,0:08:47.67,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,My husband usually returns between \N2AM and 3AM after his bar closes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.25,0:08:50.71,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Last night he said there was something \Non TV he wanted to watch
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:53.70,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and returned at 11PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:08:57.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly did he want to watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.52,0:09:03.28,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The news. An accountant \Nhe knows was arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.28,0:09:05.94,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He said he had to watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.53,0:09:10.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In this day and age, you \Ncan watch TV from anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:16.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Just knowing what happened on \Na TV program isn't evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:20.03,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You think my husband did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.03,0:09:23.87,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Despite how he seems, he despises lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.26,0:09:29.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:31.70,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something special \Nabout that figurine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.14,0:09:35.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.78,0:09:38.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a mic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.17,0:09:40.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then someone's listening \Nin on this conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.89,0:09:46.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, how did a young and \Nbeautiful woman like yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.20,0:09:49.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,end up married to that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.64,0:09:52.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you had plenty of better options.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.64,0:10:01.40,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I married him two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.02,0:10:06.00,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, I was engaged to another man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.93,0:10:12.12,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, I believed I \Nwould marry my fiancé,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.12,0:10:14.00,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but just before the wedding,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.38,0:10:18.39,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,he was stabbed by an unknown assailant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.73,0:10:30.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you lose your fiancé in the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:33.27,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He died.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.42,0:10:38.97,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit was arrested soon afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:42.58,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but they apparently died in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:11:03.93,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,After that, a series of unfortunate \Nevents occurred around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.17,0:11:06.68,DCMain,TAKASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Specifically, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.91,0:11:10.82,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The company I worked at \Nsuddenly went bankrupt,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.82,0:11:13.32,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and my sister was being stalked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.32,0:11:15.70,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,My father's factory caught fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.70,0:11:18.69,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,My mother fell off a train platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.42,0:11:21.57,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.02,0:11:24.32,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who would joke about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.97,0:11:27.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What a series of unfortunate events.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.06,0:11:34.00,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The silver lining was that none \Nof my family members died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.61,0:11:36.86,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,When I was at my lowest point,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.86,0:11:40.34,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,it was Komaki who reached out to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.10,0:11:46.67,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.28,0:11:50.71,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The hidden mic and her pleading glances.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.71,0:11:53.90,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's her life story and \Nher marriage to her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.57,0:11:57.23,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And more than anything, her expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.65,0:11:59.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you love your husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.15,0:12:00.85,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.52,0:12:02.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.86,0:12:06.48,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.48,0:12:08.62,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you ask that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.98,0:12:10.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.93,0:12:14.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask weird questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.77,0:12:18.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.28,0:12:21.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.42,0:12:28.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.10,0:12:34.44,Dec7,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,December 7th
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.10,0:12:34.44,Headlines,SIGN BLUE,0000,0000,0000,,December 7th – Events \N\NRead details of what occurred on December 7th \N\NIncidents occurring on December 7th \N\NWhat happened on December 7th
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.47,0:12:36.67,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:48.20,Text,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,From: Conan-kun \NSubject: No subject \NKogoro-no-ojisan says \Nthis room is bugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.08,0:12:48.20,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan says this room is bugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:50.70,DCItalic,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Bugged?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.32,0:12:54.52,DCItalic,TAKASHI,0000,0000,0000,,It must be her husband \NKomaki who's listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.52,0:12:56.71,DCItalic,TAKASHI,0000,0000,0000,,By why would he bug the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.27,0:13:02.46,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The wife wants to tell us the truth, but \Nshe can't because the room is bugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:08.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan says we need to communicate \Nusing something other than words.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.85,0:13:10.99,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Other than words?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.99,0:13:12.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.63,0:13:16.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, he says he'll continue \Npretending he hasn't noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:20.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're free to say you love your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.53,0:13:24.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Could I interrupt for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.06,0:13:34.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mihoko-san, could you answer the questions \NI'm about to ask you with either yes or no?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.26,0:13:35.07,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.48,0:13:39.92,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.41,0:13:43.92,DCMain,MIHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.36,0:13:45.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.06,0:13:48.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're Komaki Mihoko-san, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.00,0:13:49.91,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.99,0:13:55.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you lie about any of your testimony \Nconcerning your husband's alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.28,0:13:57.71,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.25,0:14:02.07,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,By 11PM, he had returned home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:03.98,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can vouch for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.22,0:14:08.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We already—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.38,0:14:12.57,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe your husband \Nis involved in this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.57,0:14:16.12,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm sure the culprit is someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.65,0:14:18.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then the culprit must be—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.50,0:14:21.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.64,0:14:22.38,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:25.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something preventing \Nyou from going somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.72,0:14:30.46,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here of my own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:32.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.49,0:14:38.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The police will guarantee your safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.63,0:14:40.85,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Would you be willing to help us?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.68,0:14:53.70,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.45,0:14:57.10,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,My husband will be returning soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.10,0:14:58.87,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I should cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:05.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.58,0:15:10.03,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,First I'll chop the vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.34,0:15:16.01,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.48,0:15:19.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Green onions, burdock, and daikon radishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:21.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:23.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's cooking pork soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:26.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that important?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.97,0:15:31.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If not that, then this is Morse code.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.89,0:15:35.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's pretending to chop vegetables \Nso she can tell us something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.98,0:15:50.22,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.22,0:15:51.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.72,0:15:53.30,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.70,0:15:57.43,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away from my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.06,0:15:59.02,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Komaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.02,0:16:02.06,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.29,0:16:05.69,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not going to arrest \Nme, then get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.80,0:16:10.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.34,0:16:10.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:13.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good luck charm. Well, bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.02,0:16:20.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is almost certainly \NKomaki, but we don't have evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.77,0:16:22.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If only we had concrete evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.26,0:16:24.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:25.97,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.97,0:16:28.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, did you figure something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:30.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was cooking pork soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.90,0:16:33.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After that, she'll cook \Nthe rice and a main dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.46,0:16:36.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, a pork soup \Nmade with pork belly—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.76,0:16:41.60,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.96,0:16:45.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, take us \Nto the victim's apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:46.86,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.08,0:16:52.61,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But why are we going to \Nthe victim's apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.34,0:16:59.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The first thing she was trying to tell us was \Nabout the mic hidden on the horse figurine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.18,0:17:03.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She couldn't speak freely because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.29,0:17:07.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The second thing was the art on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.52,0:17:10.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There was a date on the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.31,0:17:16.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Chiba, try searching for \Nincidents that occurred on December 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.21,0:17:19.86,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.86,0:17:20.89,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.48,0:17:23.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A slasher murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.79,0:17:26.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was probably Mihoko-san's fiancé.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.76,0:17:30.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's likely the person they \Narrested was falsely charged.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.21,0:17:33.39,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.39,0:17:34.87,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.18,0:17:39.46,DCItalic,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Like a bloody weapon, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.46,0:17:42.68,DCItalic,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Or a wine bottle with fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.68,0:17:45.79,DCItalic,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Or the jacket the culprit was wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:48.57,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,The evidence collected from \Nthe slasher murder case
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.57,0:17:51.71,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,was exactly the same as the \Nitems Komaki mentioned earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.06,0:17:58.18,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,This must be what they mean when \Nsay "bite the hand that feeds."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.06,0:18:00.68,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.90,0:18:05.83,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm disappointed. And here I \Nthought I'd taught you well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:14.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably left the same evidence at the \Ncrime scene in order to frame Hara-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.90,0:18:18.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But for some reason, the evidence was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.31,0:18:20.34,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.81,0:18:27.59,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,After I left Lisa's home, you snuck back \Ninside and took the evidence with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.59,0:18:28.58,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.88,0:18:30.41,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.41,0:18:32.34,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lie to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:35.47,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You desperately tried to tip off the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.47,0:18:37.09,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I never did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.32,0:18:42.97,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I installed a camera in the \Nstuffed bear on the sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.30,0:18:50.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the third set of fingerprints \Nfound at the crime scene were hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.28,0:18:55.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Then there's the \Nlife story she told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.11,0:18:57.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That must've been true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.06,0:19:01.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's stuck because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.98,0:19:04.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Komaki were arrested,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.21,0:19:09.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,she was probably told her family would \Nbe harmed if he learned of her betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:11.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What a awful man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:14.07,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:18.30,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. You're my precious wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.81,0:19:23.64,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But unfortunately, my precious \Nwife has gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.22,0:19:29.94,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in leaving the cops a body to \Nfind when they've already got their eyes on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.25,0:19:35.44,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, why did she \Nstart chopping vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.95,0:19:39.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That was a hint from her as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.44,0:19:40.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,A hint?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:44.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What do green onions, burdock, and \Ndaikon radishes have in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.17,0:19:45.84,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,They're used to make pork soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.84,0:19:46.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.45,0:19:48.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They're long and thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.16,0:19:50.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.22,0:19:54.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But not believing that would be enough, \Nshe began doing something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.72,0:19:57.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When Komaki showed up, the \Nrest of us weren't looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.84,0:19:59.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but Conan confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.05,0:20:03.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She chopped the vegetables and created...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.73,0:20:08.35,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like an ordinary ball-point pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.69,0:20:10.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we try disassembling it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.63,0:20:11.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:16.23,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:17.92,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's a cleaning receipt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:18.73,CleaningReceipt,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Cleaning Receipt
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.38,0:20:22.80,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We finally acquired some concrete evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.80,0:20:25.74,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,If we examine the DNA of \Nthe blood on the shirt...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.39,0:20:28.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The case is as good as solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.50,0:20:30.87,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.67,0:20:33.89,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.38,0:20:36.54,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Komaki has gone missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.54,0:20:37.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.26,0:20:41.63,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Any last words?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.98,0:20:43.95,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.95,0:20:48.46,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,She rejected my advances despite \Nthe good offer I made her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.93,0:20:51.77,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,How dare she be faithful to that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.16,0:20:53.79,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.79,0:20:56.52,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're one to talk, traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.05,0:20:59.79,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The police will arrest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.79,0:21:03.33,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think the only thing \NI did was get rid of the evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.88,0:21:04.82,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.16,0:21:09.58,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I told them everything, including \Nabout your past evils.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.57,0:21:12.93,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:17.68,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cops!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.68,0:21:18.75,DCMain,MIHOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.10,0:21:21.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because my good luck charm worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.92,0:21:29.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Police! Nobody move!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.13,0:21:33.18,DCMain,KOMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:37.02,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.26,0:21:44.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're not getting away, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.89,0:23:17.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In the investigation that followed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.48,0:23:20.08,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,it was proven that Mihoko-san's \Nfiancé's murder
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.08,0:23:23.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and crimes committed \Nby his alleged murderer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.28,0:23:25.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,were the work of Komaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.66,0:23:27.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.94,0:23:30.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you make pork soup for dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.15,0:23:33.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? You already went shopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.94,0:23:36.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about that? I want pork soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.85,0:23:39.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, pork soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.45,0:23:41.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Pork soup, pork soup, pork soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.19,0:23:42.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Green onions, burdock, and daikon radishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.67,0:23:44.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I want pork soup!
